'''Social death''' could be defined as people who are discarded from society. Examples of social death are: 

*The exclusion of women when they don't abide to the sexual rules of the family. 
*The exclusion of people who don't abide to religious rules of a certain community. Some communities exclude people with an undesired behaviour by not looking and talking with them anymore.
*Racial exclusion. Persecution of jews. Slavery. Apartheid.
*Governments can exclude individuals or groups from society. Examples: protestant minority groups in early modern Europe; ostracism in Athens; criminals; prostitutes.